theorem closureInteriorClosureInteriorClosure_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure A))))) := by
  -- First, rewrite the complicated set using an existing equality.
  have h_eq :
      closure (interior (closure (interior (closure A)))) =
        closure (interior A) :=
    (closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_eq (X := X) (A := A))
  -- We already know `P1` holds for `closure (interior A)`.
  have hP1 : Topology.P1 (closure (interior A)) :=
    closureInterior_P1 (X := X) (A := A)
  -- Transport the property along the equality.
  simpa [h_eq] using hP1
